&nbsp;
The experts of the Court of Trieste have requested an extension of two months of work to collect as much information as possible within the hearing scheduled for October. The findings refer to the attacks from 1994 to 1996 and from 2000 to 2006 in the provinces of Pordenone, Udine, Treviso and Venice. Analysis that have focused on hair formations found in a bottle of spinning stars, a tube, an egg, and on insulating tapes present in some packs of tomato and mayonnaise. The controls continued on the typhoid reliefs, on a kneeler, a box of mackerel, a device hidden under the saddle of a bicycle, and a bottle of Coca Cola.
