Maurizio Paniz, a lawyer of one of the suspects, Elvo Zornitta, has expressed all its opposition to what has been reported in the newspapers. "It is inconceivable that news that has determined the pages of today's newspapers and the defense knows nothing about it. It makes me smile that the newspapers were writing "strong detectives" and I wonder how these news came out." The lawyer has always said "happy of any investigation, of any in-depth study", but on the preservation of the finds it has "meaning doubts because in these years the manipulations can have been many and therefore I do not think it has been guaranteed the conservation". &nbsp;

